Work Ethic
  • When I am coding or designing a software system or architecting a solution, I think of the holistic business and all stakeholders when doing so. I prefer to understand and not just memorize and use. I prefer to use my creativity, my strength, to come up with my unique solutions.
  • Most people in the industry copy-paste code. I prefer to understand the system via the code example and then write unique code on my own. I make unique images on my own and will not directly download and use any image from the internet without modifying it unless it is a logo. I author all my images with GIMP (Graphical Image Manipulation Program) and demand unique artwork from colleagues I work with who are graphic artists.
  • Everything I have done has been self-taught throughout my career as I can quickly understand software, hardware and networking IT systems since childhood on my own.
  • I am very passionate about software. In 1983 I got a programmable calculator called the Sharp PC1500. It came with the Basic programming language and a slim manual that listed out the supported words of the Basic programming language. Nobody I knew was familiar with programming. Figuring out how to make video games on my own, I knew these small machines were the future. One could easily create any of your ideas on these machines with the greatest of ease. I was advised by my father to do Electrical Engineering since there were not many jobs for programming. I knew it was a matter of time before there would be. I turned out to be right. Since then, I have pursued making creative software, whether I can monetize or be rewarded in any way or not. I always name my computers after fantasy characters like one would call a pet one loves. Since I love software, I do my best on my own always with or without supervision or direction.
  • Willing to be background-checked on all my work. Have been background-checked for all my jobs in India. Always ready to be questioned about approach, methodology and am open to both positive and negative criticism and keep a positive attitude even in a negative work environment without letting my work suffer by getting affected. I am honest and transparent.
